Liberty Media Corporation (commonly referred to as Liberty Media or just Liberty) is an American mass media company controlled by chairman John C. Malone, who owns a majority of the voting shares.



Contents


1 History

1.1 The 1990s
1.2 The 2000s
1.3 The 2010s


2 Divisions

2.1 Liberty Capital

