Liberty Media Corporation

12300 Liberty Blvd. 
Englewood CO 80112 United States
Phone: +1 720-___-____
Fax: +1 720-___-____
http://www.libertymedia.com





6
Managers




225
IT employees




$232.1MEST.
IT Budget




Liberty Media Corporation is a holding company with interests in a broad range of electronic retailing, media, communications and entertainment businesses. The company's holdings include the Atlanta Braves, TruePosition, Inc. and stakes in Sirius XM Radio and Live Nation Entertainment.. … MoreLiberty Media Corporation is a holding company with interests in a broad range of electronic retailing, media, communications and entertainment businesses. The company's holdings include the Atlanta Braves, TruePosition, Inc. and stakes in Sirius XM Radio and Live Nation Entertainment..  The company sold off its Starz holding in 2013.  In 2011, Liberty Interactive, the eCommerce side of the company, was split off and made a separate, publicly traded company.
Liberty Media Corporation is a holding company with interests in a broad range of electronic retailing, media, communications and entertainment businesses. The company's holdings include the Atlanta Braves, TruePosition, Inc. and stakes in Sirius XM Radio and Live Nation Entertainment… MoreLiberty Media Corporation is a holding company with interests in a broad range of electronic retailing, media, communications and entertainment businesses. The company's holdings include the Atlanta Braves, TruePosition, Inc. and stakes in Sirius XM Radio and Live Nation Entertainment and MacNeil/Lehrer Productions.  The company sold off its Starz holding in 2013.  In 2011, Liberty Interactive, the eCommerce side of the company, was split off and made a separate, publicly traded company.

IT Priorities:
·         Company is implementing cloud solutions.
·         Infrastructure expenditures are expected to increase in data storage, remote access control, data infrastructure, disaster recovery, and virtualization.

IT Structure:
·         Liberty Media is head quartered in Englewood, CO.
·         Liberty Media Corporation maintains many subsidiary companies with independent IT departments.
·         In 2012, the company announced that it planned in 2013 to spin off Starz LLC as an independent company.
·         In 2011, the company split off its eCommerce division (Liberty Interactive) into its own separate company, which is maintained as a separate profile in the RainKing database, as is Liberty Media's Sirius XM subsidiary.
·         Additionally, Liberty Media co-owns MacNeil/Lehrer Productions with the two former co-anchors of the program; MacNeil/Lehrer employs its own IT personnel. Liberty Capital, a division of Liberty Media, also owns TruePosition and the Atlanta Braves, the latter of which has a lean IT department.
·         The IT budget is typically finalized in Q4.

IT Vendors:
·         Liberty Media maintains SOX compliance through a software-as-a-service (SaaS) product by Aline.

IT Intelligence Snippets:
2013:
·         Q1 2013, Liberty Media Corporation is planning to increase security spending in digital rights management, encryption, enterprise security management, mobile security, storage security and contingency and continuity.
·         1-5 pb data volume company-wide across 2 to 5 data centers, and expects an annual data growth of 6-10%.
·         75-90% of its servers are to be virtualized by the end of 2013.
·         Corporate IT manages 500 mobile devices, while 100 are managed elsewhere.
·         Corporate IT manages 1000 desktops, while 100 are managed elsewhere.
·         Standardized on 1-2 product vendors with a limited set of hardware.
·         Long term plan for running new applications is to add servers and virtualize, but no new facilities are scheduled.





